props.text: As of January 1, 2025, we’ve phased out conventional chicken and committed to serving higher-welfare chicken throughout all Novo Nordisk locations. Switching to welfare-certified chicken is a meaningful choice —for both animal welfare and the quality of the food we serve. These chickens grow more slowly and live under better conditions, with more space, access to daylight, and the ability to express natural behaviors. The result is meat with richer flavor and better texture. We believe small changes in daily choices can make a big difference. By choosing higher-welfare chicken, we’re taking a step toward a more responsible and sustainable food culture. And we hope you can taste the difference. Thank you for eating with care💚

props.subTitle:
With the collaboration between Novo Nordisk and Compass Group, we are running the biggest catering contract in Danish history. Every day, we serve more than 15.000 meals in 45 different locations. This includes 5 cafés and Novo Nordisk’s own Favrholm Campus.

At our core, we strive to produce healthy and environmentally sustainable meals that not only nourish the body but also respect the planet. With a focus to sourcing local, organic ingredients whenever possible, we aim to minimize our ecological footprint while maximizing flavor and nutrition.

Together, let's savor the joy of good food that not only delights the senses but also nourishes the soul.

Our Chef Apprentices!
props.subTitle:
At Compass Group we give considerable importance to our chef apprentices, their development and training are at the core of our mission. As the foodservice provider for Novo Nordisk, we are always striving to be even better, devoting significant effort towards ensuring that the education our chef apprentices receive, reflects their hard work and commitment. Compass Group has, in fact, dedicated the largest number of our chef apprentices to the Novo Nordisk contract.

Additionally, our chef apprentices participate in internal competitions designed to foster a spirit of friendly rivalry and to the continuous sharpening of their skills. Each quarter, the winning dish from these competitions is featured on our menu at every Novo Nordisk location, showcasing the exceptional talent of our chef apprentices and allowing them to contribute directly to our culinary offerings.
 
The next winning dish will be featured in your canteen on Friday the 27th of March 2026.

We believe providing our chef apprentices with these opportunities, creates the ideal base for future career growth. Please give them a high-five or a friendly smile, next time you see one of our students behind the counter!

text.description/text: Collect your goods and swipe in the app

props.text: As of January 2025, we have taken another step toward more responsible and sustainable food choices in our canteen: We have phased out conventional eggs in favor of organic eggs.   At Novo Nordisk, we take responsibility for what ends up on your plate. That is why we now use organic eggs from hens raised under high animal-welfare standards – with access to outdoor space, fresh air, and a natural diet free from synthetic pesticides, hormones, and antibiotics.   For us, it is not just about nutrition. It is about choosing ingredients that reflect our values: protecting animal welfare, supporting sustainable agriculture, and providing food you can trust. You should never have to wonder what kind of egg is in your meal. We have already made that decision – with care.   Thank you for helping us support better animal welfare🙏

text.receiptNote/text: You can collect your Take Away in the fridge in the canteen next to the staircase after 1:00 pm
text.noCategory/text: Take Away is served with a side salad.
text.description/text: Preorder from the menu here. Take Away is served with a side salad.

props.title: Together we fight food waste
props.subtitle: In week 39, we marked Novo Nordisk Climate Week. We reduced our food waste by 6% compared to our usual levels. This initiative is part of our ongoing effort to raise awareness about food waste and show how small daily choices can make a big difference. By only taking what you can eat, you not only reduce waste but also help lower our collective environmental footprint. 👏 A big thank you to everyone who joined the challenge and supported Climate Week. Let’s keep the good habits going – every plate counts! And don’t forget, you can also help reduce waste by buying leftovers to take home.

props.title: Take Away

props.subTitle:
With the collaboration between Novo Nordisk and Compass Group, we are running the biggest catering contract in Danish history. Every day, we serve more than 15.000 meals in 45 different locations. This includes 5 cafés and Novo Nordisk’s own Favrholm Campus.

At our core, we strive to produce healthy and environmentally sustainable meals that not only nourish the body but also respect the planet. With a focus to sourcing local, organic ingredients whenever possible, we aim to minimize our ecological footprint while maximizing flavor and nutrition.

Together, let's savor the joy of good food that not only delights the senses but also nourishes the soul.

Our Chef Apprentices!
props.subTitle:
At Compass Group we give considerable importance to our chef apprentices, their development and training are at the core of our mission. As the foodservice provider for Novo Nordisk, we are always striving to be even better, devoting significant effort towards ensuring that the education our chef apprentices receive, reflects their hard work and commitment. Compass Group has, in fact, dedicated the largest number of our chef apprentices to the Novo Nordisk contract.

Additionally, our chef apprentices participate in internal competitions designed to foster a spirit of friendly rivalry and to the continuous sharpening of their skills. Each quarter, the winning dish from these competitions is featured on our menu at every Novo Nordisk location, showcasing the exceptional talent of our chef apprentices and allowing them to contribute directly to our culinary offerings.
 
The next winning dish will be featured in your canteen on Friday the 27th of March 2026.

We believe providing our chef apprentices with these opportunities, creates the ideal base for future career growth. Please give them a high-five or a friendly smile, next time you see one of our students behind the counter!

props.text: As of January 1, 2025, we’ve phased out conventional chicken and committed to serving higher-welfare chicken throughout all Novo Nordisk locations. Switching to welfare-certified chicken is a meaningful choice —for both animal welfare and the quality of the food we serve. These chickens grow more slowly and live under better conditions, with more space, access to daylight, and the ability to express natural behaviors. The result is meat with richer flavor and better texture. We believe small changes in daily choices can make a big difference. By choosing higher-welfare chicken, we’re taking a step toward a more responsible and sustainable food culture. And we hope you can taste the difference. Thank you for eating with care💚

props.title: Together we fight food waste
props.subtitle: In week 39, we marked Novo Nordisk Climate Week. We reduced our food waste by 6% compared to our usual levels. This initiative is part of our ongoing effort to raise awareness about food waste and show how small daily choices can make a big difference. By only taking what you can eat, you not only reduce waste but also help lower our collective environmental footprint. 👏 A big thank you to everyone who joined the challenge and supported Climate Week. Let’s keep the good habits going – every plate counts! And don’t forget, you can also help reduce waste by buying leftovers to take home.

props.text: As of January 2025, we have taken another step toward more responsible and sustainable food choices in our canteen: We have phased out conventional eggs in favor of organic eggs.   At Novo Nordisk, we take responsibility for what ends up on your plate. That is why we now use organic eggs from hens raised under high animal-welfare standards – with access to outdoor space, fresh air, and a natural diet free from synthetic pesticides, hormones, and antibiotics.   For us, it is not just about nutrition. It is about choosing ingredients that reflect our values: protecting animal welfare, supporting sustainable agriculture, and providing food you can trust. You should never have to wonder what kind of egg is in your meal. We have already made that decision – with care.   Thank you for helping us support better animal welfare🙏

items.description:
It’s finally here!
The “fastelavnsbolle” has arrived and can now be purchased through our convenience app and in our cafés.
This year, we’re taking a nostalgic trip back in time. Our talented bakers and pastry chefs have crafted an old-school version with creamy vanilla in the middle and a chocolate topping.
Take them home and enjoy them with friends and family.
Be sure to order yours today and pick them up freshly baked tomorrow!

Danish Version:
Så er den her!
Fastelavnsbollen er ankommet og kan nu købes igennem vores convenience app og i vores caféer.
I år tager vi en tur tilbage i tiden, hvor vores dygtige bagere og konditorer har lavet en gammeldags udgave med vaniljecreme i midten og chokolade på toppen.
Tag dem med hjem og nyd dem med venner og familie.
Bestil den i dag og hent den helt friskbagt i morgen!
